name: 5-methyl-3-(2,4,6-trimethylphenyl)-1H-pyrazole
source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-2485
Reason: 5-methyl-3-(2,4,6-trimethylphenyl)-1H-pyrazole has a melting point that can be predicted by considering its structural components. The basic unit is pyrazole, which has a melting point of around 100°C. The methyl group adds approximately +10°C due to increased molecular weight and rigidity. The 2,4,6-trimethylphenyl group can contribute approximately +30°C due to increased molecular weight and the presence of three methyl groups, which can participate in hydrogen bonding and dipole interactions. The pyrazole ring itself can also contribute approximately +10°C due to its rigidity and potential hydrogen bonding.
